SUMMARY:Urbanist GOTV (with Dallas Neighbors for Housing, Dallas Area Transit Alliance, and DFW Urbanistas)
DESCRIPTION:Dallas has the lowest voter turnout of any major US city. Because of that\, we continue to see a Dallas where change is slow. We are still a city built where the status quo of driving a car for every trip\, dangerous and inaccessible streets\, and single family housing no matter what\, remain the standard in Dallas.\n\nJoin together with Urbanist groups of Dallas to go to the polls. Vote for a walkable\, bikeable\, transit rich\, affordable Dallas. Vote for Urbanism.\nRSVP on Action Network is appreciated.\n\nhttps://actionnetwork.org/events/urbanist-get-out-the-vote\n\n\nDetails:\n\nSunday\, April 27\n\n12:20 Optional \n@urbanistasdfw\n Transit Together at Mockingbird Station or Bishop Arts Streetcar Station\n\n1:00pm Gather and Group Photo at West End Square\n\n1:30pm Vote at Dallas Records Building\n\n3:00pm (or immediately after voting) Social at Pegasus Brewing Company\n\n***Walking\, biking\, taking transit is highly encouraged!\n\nUrbanist GOTV is a collaboration between Dallas urbanist groups:\n\n@ridewithdata\n\n\n@dallasbicyclecoalition\n\n\n@neighborsdtx\n\n\n@dallasurbanists\n\n\n@urbanistasdfw\n\n\nThis event is strictly to encourage people to vote and does not endorse any particular candidate. Any Dallas County voter is eligible to vote at any early voting location and is welcome to vote with us at the Dallas County Records Building. See more at Dallascountyvotes.org.\n
LOCATION:West End Square 607 Corbin St Dallas, TX 75202
X-ORGANIZING-GROUP:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
