SUMMARY:A Night of Good Trouble: College of Constructive Hellraising Graduation
DESCRIPTION:Dallas Bicycle Coalition was one of 10 organizations to participate in the College of Constructive Hellraising this spring. Come to our graduation. The event is free\, but please RSVP for food. https://www.eventbrite.com/e/a-night-of-good-trouble-tickets-1349755086799?\n````````````````````````````````````````````\nCome join us for a night of good trouble featuring Jerry Hawkins speaking on "How Change Happens in Dallas"\, the annual \nCollege of Constructive Hell-Raising\n graduation ceremony\, \na brand new competition among DFW grassroots groups for the best project pitch\,\n AND the debut of an importanty \nnew Dallas voting alliance.\n Free food. Free information. Free entertainment. Y'all come.\n\nAbout the College:\n Since 2017 The \nCollege of Constructive\n \nHell-Raising\,\n has offered an annual semester-long class about how to win grassroots Change. We draw on our three decades of experience as well as the history of those DFW elders and peers who’ve taught us with their own examples. Unlike other seminars for political activists\, the College isn’t issue or skill-specific. It’s about the mechanics of how you win grassroots fights with grassroots resources\, no matter the cause. Our goal is for graduates to \n“think like an organizer.”\nAbout the Organizing School\n: The Organizing School is a collection of North Texas community organizers and change-makers that span generations and causes. We’ve come together to share our collective knowledge\, skills\, and expertise to our peers who are seeking their own change.\n
LOCATION:Four Corners Brewery: 1311 S Ervay St
