UID:dbc_a4c8c244-5c18-4966-a1bb-754b6bbb2f0b
DTSTAMP:20260217T204255Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20251028T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20251028T183000
SUMMARY:West Davis Complete Street Public Meeting
DESCRIPTION:​​The West Davis Street Project is a Complete Streets redesign between ​Cockrell Hill Road and Clinton Avenue. The project has several key goals\, including improving conditions for walking and biking\, providing a more robust connection between neighborhoods\, calming traffic\, and improving overall safety along the West Davis corridor. See more: https://dallascityhall.com/departments/transportation/Pages/west-davis-street-project.aspx\n\nFollowing the meeting\, residents are invited to participate in a survey regarding preferred roadway alignments for Phase 1. \nThe survey and meeting materials will be made available at 5:30 p.m. on October 28\, 2025.\n\nSee more public meetings from Dallas Department of Transportation and Public Works: https://dallascityhall.com/departments/transportation/Pages/public-meetings.aspx\n\n\n\n\n
LOCATION:Saint Cecilia Catholic School (635 Mary Cliff Road, Dallas, TX 75208)
X-ORGANIZING-GROUP:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-TEAMUP-WHO:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-EVENT-TYPE:social_gathering
X-REJECTED:false
