SUMMARY:Impacts of Legislative Reform on the Housing Crisis (Learn how newlegislation from Austin & Dallas could unlock a wave of affordable housing & suburban retrofit. Hear from our panel!)
DESCRIPTION:Who: Learn how new legislation from Austin & Dallas could unlock a wave of affordable housing & suburban retrofit. Hear from our panel!\n\nLearn how new legislation from Austin &amp\; Dallas could unlock a wave of affordable housing &amp\; suburban retrofit. Hear from our panel!New tools to address the housing crisis: legislative change in Austin and Dallas could spur a new wave of affordable housing and suburban retrofit.  \nListen to an array of perspectives to learn about the shifting legislative landscape at both the State and local level which may lower long time hurdles that prevented residential and mixed use development. Our panel of developers\, municipalities\, and urban planning strategies will discuss the impacts of these legislative changes on incremental development\, suburban retrofits\, and housing affordability.Panelist:Emily Liu Director of Planning\, City of DallasMonte Anders President\, Options Real EstatePatrick KennedyKevin Shepherd President\, Verdunity\n\n
LOCATION:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/impacts-of-zoning-reform-legislative-changes-tickets-1770798448829
