DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20251119T200000
SUMMARY:Bike Streets App Launch and Group Ride
DESCRIPTION:Dallas Bicycle Coalition is partnering with Bike Streets to provide a routing tool that navigates anyone on a bike to safe\, low stress streets and trails across Dallas. Ever had google maps drop you on the side of highway?? Bike Streets solves that problem and encourages all levels of cyclists to travel safely by bike.\n\nDBC volunteers have been working since July to map out the best low- stress bike routes in Dallas (even if that sometimes means a sidewalk). The first version of the map is public! \nhttps://www.bikestreets.com/tx/dallas/bike-map/\n\nAnd now\, we're launching to a broader audience! We need DBC members to ride with the app to test the map and add all the best routes near you.Join us on Wednesday\, Nov 19 to ride with the lead DBC Bike Streets volunteer\, Jason G\, through the Design District. Learn how to use the app and contribute to its development. Bring your bike\, helmet\, and lights for an easy paced social ride.\n\nLastly\, make sure you're on the dbc email list by Monday\, Nov 17. We're sharing a limited opportunity for a year free of the app. \ndallasbicyclecoalition.org/signup\n
LOCATION:The Meteor Cafe: 1950 Hi Line Dr.
X-ORGANIZING-GROUP:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-TEAMUP-WHO:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-EVENT-TYPE:social_gathering
X-REJECTED:false
CREATED:20251111T221747Z
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dbc_8c16004d-57be-4b7b-a553-ae2b949cf511
DTSTAMP:20260217T204255Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Chicago:20251119T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Chicago:20251119T220000
SUMMARY:Upshift Awards
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: BikeDFW\nTickets: https://www.zeffy.com/en-US/ticketing/2025-bikedfw-upshift-awards\nFor every trail mile\, bike lane\, bike rack & repair station\; and for every increase in funding for active transportation\; and for every new person getting out and riding their bike\, there is a person\, organization\, agency or business that has been doing the hard work of making the Dallas-Fort Worth region a better place to walk and bike.\n​\nWe are incredibly excited to have a chance to recognize those who encourage\, champion\, and inspire us with their commitment\, and are making significant contributions to bicycling and active transportation in DFW. We hope you will join us in celebrating these individuals and groups for all they are doing in the region.\nVoting for the 2025 cohort is happening NOW until 11/18 at \nhttps://docs.google.com/.../1FAIpQLSdrDXeozch.../viewform...\nThen we celebrate to our heroes on Wednesday\, 11/19 at Four Corners Brewing!!\n
LOCATION:Four Corners Brewing Co
X-ORGANIZING-GROUP:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-TEAMUP-WHO:Dallas Bicycle Coalition
X-EVENT-TYPE:social_gathering
X-REJECTED:false
CREATED:20251111T222115Z
END:VEVENT
