SUMMARY:Cranksgiving 2025
DESCRIPTION:Hosted by: BikeDFW\nSee more: https://www.facebook.com/events/819330800813373/\nJoin BikeDFW for the wildest food drive on two wheels — part ride\, part scavenger hunt\, all heart. PLEASE RSVP at \nhttps://forms.gle/S6cZNJfyfexP7Zp46\n ("ticket" = RSVP)\n\nCranksgiving Dallas 2025 is a free\, city-wide bike ride and food drive benefiting Owenwood Farm & Neighbor Space. Riders visit grocery stores across Dallas to purchase food and household items for donation — then celebrate at White Rock Ale House with prizes\, cheers\, and high-fives.\n\nStart your morning at Merit Coffee – Deep Ellum for check-in\, coffee\, and good vibes.\nWheels down at 10:45 AM — plan your own route\, ride safely\, and keep every receipt!\nAll items must be purchased during the ride ($15-$20 recommended).\nCostumes encouraged — shenanigans inevitable.\n\nStart Location:\nMerit Coffee – Deep Ellum\n2639 Main St\, Dallas TX 75226\nFinish Location:\nWhite Rock Alehouse & Brewery**\n7331 Gaston Ave.\, Dallas TX 75214\n**NOTE: Change in ending address**\n
LOCATION:Merit Coffee Deep Ellum
