SUMMARY:Busy
DESCRIPTION:Join us<b> Saturday\, 2/7 at 10:00 AM f</b>or a door-knocking canvass to remind voters about the May DART election. We’ll be encouraging Irving residents to vote YES to keep public transit in our city.<br><br>Never door-knocked before? <b>We'll pair you with someone more experienced!<br></b><br>All door-knockers must sign-up before the canvassing.<br><br><a href="https://actionnetwork.org/events/vote-yes-for-dart-irving-canvassing-kickoff/">Click this registration link to sign-up.</a><br><br>We’ll kick things off with a brief canvassing training at Cottonwood Creek Park\, then head out together. <br>We’ll be <b>canvassing in teams of three</b>—one person with a car and two people door-knocking—to help us move faster and reach more voters.<br><br>What to bring:<br><ul><li>Comfortable walking shoes</li><li>Layered clothing</li><li>The MiniVAN app downloaded before you arrive</li></ul><br>See you out there! 🚶‍♀️🚶‍♂️
LOCATION:Cottonwood Creek Park\, 4051 N Story Rd\, Irving\, TX 75038\, USA
